## Architecture Documentation

**Vendor abstraction rule (CLAUDE.md line 56)**: `Vendor abstractions: Standalone re-exports of third-party SDKs. Never import @planetscale/* directly → use @vendor/db`.

The current `vendor/db/src/index.ts` only re-exports drizzle's SQL utilities (`and`, `eq`, `desc`, etc.) and `alias`. It does **not** expose driver constructors. So `db/app/src/client.ts` imports `@neondatabase/serverless`, `drizzle-orm/neon-http`, `drizzle-orm/postgres-js`, and `postgres` directly. This is a longstanding gap — fixing it is its own refactor (Theme 4 Option C).

**`@lightfastai/dev-proxy/projects` `withProject` vs `resolveProjectUrl`**:
- `withProject({ projectName, defaultHost })` — returns the resolved URL or `defaultHost` fallback. Used in `apps/app/next.config.ts:25`, `apps/app/src/lib/project-urls.ts:7`, `apps/platform/src/lib/project-urls.ts:9`.
- `resolveProjectUrl("name")` — returns `null` when VRP isn't set. Used in `apps/www/src/lib/project-urls.ts:4`.

The `defaultHost` fallback is the source of the Theme 5 bug — it conflates "production" with "preview".

**Auth one-shot effect pattern**: three components (`otp-island.tsx`, `session-activator.tsx`, `client-auth-bridge.tsx`) all latch a `useRef<boolean>` to prevent duplicate execution, but all three set the latch *before* the async work succeeds. Same fix shape applies to all three.

